President Mohammadu Buhari on Tuesday approved the reappointment of Mr Segun Adeyemi and Mr Williams Adeleye as his Special Assistants (Media) attached to the Office of the Minister of Information and Culture, Alh. Lai Mohammed. Their appointment letters, which were signed by the Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Mr Boss Mustapha, said the appointment took effect from 6th September, 2019. ALSO READ: Ministers to submit report December, Osinbajo says Mr Adeyemi and Mr Williams served in the same capacity between November 2015 and May 2019. Vanguard President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the re-appointment of Mr. Segun Adeyemi and Mr. Williams Adeleye as his Special Assistants (Media) attached to the Office of the Minister of Information and Culture. September 17, 2019 In "News" President Muhammadu Buhari has re-appointed Mr Ade Ipaye as Deputy Chief of Staff to the President, Laolu Akande, Senior Special Assistant to the President on Media and Publicity Office of the Vice President, says. August 22, 2019 In "News" Ex-President Olusegun Obasanjo’s media aide, Mr. Kehinde Adeyemi has on Wednesday denied Obasanjo’s involvement in endorsing President Muhammadu Buhari’s second term bid. May 2, 2018 In "News"